arneis string quartet the bridal canopy by jonathan berger events at stanford arneis string quartet the bridal canopy by jonathan berger facebook twitter email print add to calendar arneis string quartet is joined by stanford faculty composer jonathan berger for a performance and discussion of berger's fourth string quartet the bridal canopy the work commissioned for the st lawrence string quartet and premiered in 2008 is based on the story of the same name by the israeli author and nobel laureate shmuel agnon hakhnasat kallah as the story is called in hebrew describes the fictional wanderings of the quixote like hasid reb yudel through the jewish villages of galicia at the beginning of the 19th century in search of a bridegroom and a dowry for his daughter for this program arneis performs berger's work in its entirety and berger illustrates some of the compositional techniques he has employed to evoke this story through music when wednesday february 22 2012 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.0 hour s where campbell recital hall braun music center map audience general public faculty staff students tags arts performance humanities music sponsor stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 311 31167 more info last modified february 22 2012
